02/11/2005
SANDANSKI, Bulgaria -- Interior Minister Rumen Petkov and Macedonian counterpart Ljubomir Mihajlovski met in Sandanski on Tuesday (1 November) to discuss ways to further enhance bilateral co-operation.
The talks, also attended by regional police chiefs from the two neighbouring countries, focused on joint measures against terrorism, money laundering and organised crime.
In other news Tuesday, a court in Sofia issued a permanent detention measure for two alleged mafia bosses, accused in connection with three contract murders.
The two brothers were arrested as part of a nationwide sweep against organised crime, launched after the murder of prominent banker Emil Kyulev.
(BNR - 01/11/05)
